<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="170" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[835,1443,473,818]" pageId="8" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,974,508,532]" pageId="8" pageNumber="170">Comments.</emphasis>
This is an undescribed species resembling 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DeWalt &amp; Stark" authorityYear="1998" box="[976,1103,544,568]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Perlesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="golconda">
<emphasis box="[976,1103,544,568]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="170">P. golconda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but distinctive according to unique aedeagal characteristics. Our material has been collected from the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:D66F87C9962BFFFCFC96C78AB4E13064:5B196004962BFFFCFB89C434B2373129" box="[1116,1327,615,639]" name="Menominee River" pageId="8" pageNumber="170" stateProvince="Wisconsin">Menominee River</location>
along the Michigan-Wisconsin border, yet on the 
<collectingRegion box="[1321,1443,651,675]" country="United States of America" name="Wisconsin" pageId="8" pageNumber="170">Wisconsin</collectingRegion>
side. We consider this a valid 
<collectingRegion box="[1233,1345,686,710]" country="United States of America" name="Michigan" pageId="8" pageNumber="170">Michigan</collectingRegion>
record. Formal description will follow once gravid females are obtained to permit scanning electron microscopy of mature eggs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
